statement.p:
Prove that the following matrices are orthogonal. Are any of these matrices in SO(n)?



\begin{pmatrix}
						1/\sqrt{2} & -1/\sqrt{2} \\
						1/\sqrt{2} & 1/\sqrt{2}
						\end{pmatrix}


\begin{pmatrix}
						1 / \sqrt{5} & 2 / \sqrt{5} \\
						- 2 /\sqrt{5} & 1/ \sqrt{5}
						\end{pmatrix}


\begin{pmatrix}
						4/ \sqrt{5} & 0 & 3 / \sqrt{5} \\
						-3 / \sqrt{5} & 0 & 4 / \sqrt{5} \\
						0 & -1 & 0
						\end{pmatrix}


\begin{pmatrix}
						1/3 & 2/3 & - 2/3 \\
						- 2/3 & 2/3 & 1/3 \\
						-2/3 & 1/3 & 2/3
						\end{pmatrix}

Verify that
				E(n) = \{(A, {\mathbf x}) : A \in O(n) \text{ and } {\mathbf x} \in {\mathbb R}^n \}
			is a group.
